    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1403247946,
    "creation_date" : 1403247946,
    "answer_id" : 24321734,
    "question_id" : 5323502,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The accepted answer has to be really altered otherwise not working. The <strong>getDecimalFormatSymbols</strong> makes a defensive copy. Thus,</p>\n\n<pre><code>DecimalFormat formatter = (DecimalFormat) NumberFormat.getInstance(Locale.US);\nDecimalFormatSymbols symbols = formatter.getDecimalFormatSymbols();\n\nsymbols.setGroupingSeparator(' ');\nformatter.setDecimalFormatSymbols(symbols);\nSystem.out.println(formatter.format(bd.longValue()));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The new line is this one: <strong>formatter.setDecimalFormatSymbols(symbols);</strong></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2386830,
      "reputation" : 8350,
      "user_id" : 2087640,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 82,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/1buts.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Gab",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2087640/gab"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1411982470,
    "creation_date" : 1411982470,
    "answer_id" : 26096479,
    "question_id" : 5323502,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>NumberFormat nf = DecimalFormat.getInstance(myLocale);\nDecimalFormatSymbols customSymbol = new DecimalFormatSymbols();\ncustomSymbol.setDecimalSeparator(',');\ncustomSymbol.setGroupingSeparator(' ');\n((DecimalFormat)nf).setDecimalFormatSymbols(customSymbol);\nnf.setGroupingUsed(true);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3406565,
      "reputation" : 4043,
      "user_id" : 2857477,
      "user_type" : "registered",
